column5: I went out for about 3 hours this morning out of bluffers and hooked into a small shaker, saw a few boat around me boat some fish.  If you were out there, how did you do?
I was out Wednesday and Friday out of Darlington .Landed a 1  chinook each  day over 20 . Down 65ft in 115 ft . Both times on rocket on rigger. Was solo so pictures are off.
Could you show a pic of your rigger set up ship? Nice fish btw.
Large rye davis teaser head with MC Rocket soaked in homemade fish scent. I was out today Monday July 13/09. and landed 3 on green rocket. Here is a picture of the setup.
